      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based discretization error estimate below 5% for NIH QoI on production mesh; grid convergence index reported.",
      "rationale": "Grid convergence study performed on three mesh levels (4M, 12M, 36M cells). GCI for NIH is 14.2%, well above the 5% threshold. Rotating-stator interface treatment introduces non-monotonic convergence at fine levels. Achieved Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match VAD operating envelope (flow 3–8 L/min, speed 2400–3600 RPM) with full documentation of blood analogue properties and temperature control.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments cover 2 of 5 required VAD operating points. Blood analogue (glycerol-water) viscosity deviates from porcine blood rheology by up to 18% at shear rates below 100 s⁻¹. Temperature control documented to ±1°C. Achieved Gradation 3; two gradations below MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel) below 10% for NIH across all validation operating points; uncertainty in experimental measurements fully characterized.",
      "rationale": "Mean relative error across two validated operating points is 22.4%. Experimental uncertainty (±8% NIH) is documented. Systematic over-prediction at high flow is attributed to turbulence model deficiency in tip-clearance region. Achieved Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
